    {
      "id": "bf19ed07-b293-4511-82e0-cb39fcf6cc55",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In order to address this, the authors propose a temporal DL model that predicts the probability of a student dropping out or not. The model outperforms other baseline algorithms tested while also returning a probability → meaning that educators can start by trying to help students flagged as more likely to drop out relative to other colleagues.",
